Hello,

I was able to access and install the dependent LSP4IJ plugin, and after adding it, the Liberty Tools plugin worked successfully.

The steps shared in the attached email were helpful, especially for completing the prerequisite setup. I have included the working steps below for reference.

1. Install the LSP4IJ prerequisite plugin
   1. Download the ZIP file.
   2. In IntelliJ, go to Preferences > Plugins > Install Plugin from Disk.
   3. Select the downloaded ZIP file, confirm the installation, and restart the IDE.

2. Install the Liberty Tools plugin
   1. Download the latest ZIP file from the GitHub releases page.
   2. In IntelliJ, go to Preferences > Plugins > Install Plugin from Disk.
   3. Select the downloaded ZIP file, confirm the installation, and restart the IDE.

Please let me know if needed, and I can share the download links as well.

